 an interview format with the author or written by themselves. Each author communicates either by typing or by a combination of speech and typing. These chapters are framed by a substantive introduction and conclusion that contextualize the book, the methodology, and the analysis, and situate it within a critical disability studies framework. The volume allows a look into the rich and insightful perspectives of people who have heretofore been thought of as uninterested in the world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAutism. 0aAutistic peoplevBiography. 0aAutistic peoplexLanguage. 0aAutistic peoplexPatientsvBiography. 0aAutistic peoplexPatientsxLanguage. 7aPSYCHOLOGY / Psychopathology / Autism Spectrum Disorders.2bisacsh1 aAttfield, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBissonnette, Larry, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBlackman, Lucy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9780814787052.001.0001zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814787052zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780814787052/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA